{
  "text": "By contrast, there was no significant correlation between maternal age and offspring telomere length. Following [CITATION_1] , assuming both parents to contribute equally to telomere length of offspring, the non-significant negative slope of 215 (+16 s.e., x 2 1 ¼ 0:84, p ¼ 0.36; figure 1b; electronic supplementary material, table S1) was close to that expected from the paternal age estimate and the correlation between paternal and maternal age (r ¼ 0.58): 0.58 Â 235 ¼ 220 base pairs.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "67858822"
